{"title_page": "Chhattisgarh Swami Vivekanand Technical University", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=August 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Infobox University\n|name           = Chhattisgarh Swami Vivekanand Technical University\n|image          = Chhattisgarh Swami Vivekanand Technical University transparent logo.png\n|motto          =\"Arise! Awake! and stop not until the goal is reached.\" \n|established    = {{start date|2005}}\n|vice_chancellor     = M.K. Verma \n|city           = [[Bhilai]], [[Chhattisgarh]], [[India]]\n|country        =India\n|students=\n|type           = [[Public university|Public]] [[State University]]\n|campus         = [[Urban areas|Urban]]\n|affiliations   = [[University Grants Commission (India)|UGC]], [[All India Council of Technical Education|AICTE]]\n|website= [http://www.csvtu.ac.in www.csvtu.ac.in]\n|logo           =|logo_size=250px\n|Address=}}\n'''Chhattisgarh Swami Vivekanand Technical University''' ('''CSVTU''') is a Public State University located in [[Bhilai]], [[Chhattisgarh]], [[India]]. On 30 April 2005, the foundation stone of the University was laid by the Prime Minister of India [[Manmohan Singh]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.csvtu.ac.in/ew/|title=Chhattisgarh Swami Vivekanand Technical University \u2013 CSVTU|language=en-US|access-date=2019-02-11}}</ref><ref name=\"Bhilai Steel Plant gives land for tech university\">{{cite news|title=Bhilai Steel Plant gives land for tech university |url=http://www.indiaedunews.net/Chhattisgarh/Bhilai_Steel_Plant_gives_land_for_tech_university_3096/ |accessdate=9 July 2013 |newspaper=India Edunews |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6HyVNzhEA?url=http://www.indiaedunews.net/Chhattisgarh/Bhilai_Steel_Plant_gives_land_for_tech_university_3096/ |archivedate=9 July 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref><ref name=\"HEoI Chhattisgarh Swami Vivekanand Technical University\">{{cite news|title=Chhattisgarh Swami Vivekanand Technical University|url=http://www.highereducationinindia.com/universities/chhattisgarh-swami-vivekananda.php|accessdate=9 July 2013|newspaper=Higher Education on India|authorlink=https://www.webcitation.org/6HyXSWIr3?url=http://www.highereducationinindia.com/universities/chhattisgarh-swami-vivekananda.php}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\n\n=== Establishment ===\nIn early 2005 the State Government of Chhattisgarh decided to establish the University with the aim of providing \"systematic, efficient and quality education\" in the fields of engineering and technology. The relevant act was passed in the Chhattisgarh state assembly on 21 January 2005. [[Manmohan Singh]], then [[Prime Minister of India]], laid the foundation stone of the University in a ceremony held on 30 April 2005.<ref name=\"Bhilai Steel Plant gives land for tech university\" />\n\n=== Land and financial aid by Bhilai Steel Plant ===\nAccording to a 2008 news report, the [[Bhilai Steel Plant]], one of the largest steel plants of the country, agreed to donate over 250 acres of land to the Chhattisgarh government for the establishment of the University, along with {{INRConvert|500|m}} for related infrastructure development.<ref name=\"Bhilai Steel Plant gives land for tech university\" />\n\n=== Adopting industry-academia linkage system ===\nAfter the University adopted an \"industry-academia linkage system\", a similar system was adopted by five other state universities. The system apparently offers financial rewards for students working on industry-defined problems.<ref name=\"5 tech varsities follow GTU model\">{{cite news|title=5 tech varsities follow GTU model |url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/5-tech-varsities-follow-GTU-model/865580/ |accessdate=9 July 2013 |newspaper=Indian Express |date=26 October 2011 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6HyZN0d0v?url=http://www.indianexpress.com/news/5-tech-varsities-follow-GTU-model/865580/ |archivedate=9 July 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref>\n== Management ==\n\n=== Faculties ===\n{{As of|2013}} the University offers courses in seven sections which are: Engineering & Technology, Applied Science, Management & Entrepreneurship, Pharmacy, Architecture, Humanities and Ecology & Environment.<ref name=\"CSVTU results 2011 declared\">{{cite news|title=CSVTU results 2011 declared |url=http://english.samaylive.com/lifestyle/education-news/676481192/csvtu-results-2011-declared.html |accessdate=9 July 2013 |newspaper=Samay Live |date=22 January 2011 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6HyXuaC4n?url=http://english.samaylive.com/lifestyle/education-news/676481192/csvtu-results-2011-declared.html |archivedate=9 July 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref><ref name=\"(official website) CSVTU faculty\">{{cite web|title=CSVTU faculty |url=http://csvtu.ac.in/faculties.htm |publisher=CSVTU |accessdate=9 July 2013 |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6HyYKWuLy?url=http://csvtu.ac.in/faculties.htm |archivedate=9 July 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy }}</ref>\n\n=== Reservation of seats for SAIL ===\n\nWhile the University was still in the planning stage, it was reported that 50 percent of certain postgraduate courses would be reserved for employees of the [[Steel Authority of India]] (SAIL), while a small number of places in other courses would be reserved for their children.<ref name=\"Bhilai Steel Plant gives land for tech university\" />\n\n=== Affiliations ===\nThe University affiliates a substantial number of Engineering and Polytechnics colleges in Chhattisgarh: over 60 Engineering colleges and 30 Polytechnics colleges are affiliated.<ref name=\"(official website) Affliated Engineering Colleges\">{{cite web|title=Affiliated Engineering Colleges|url=http://csvtu.ac.in/pdf_doc/affiliated_engg%20_colleges%20with%20CSVTU.pdf|publisher=CSVTU|accessdate=9 July 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130820190429/http://csvtu.ac.in/pdf_doc/affiliated_engg%20_colleges%20with%20CSVTU.pdf|archivedate=20 August 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"(official website) Affiliated Polytechnics colleges\">{{cite web|title=Affiliated Polytechnics colleges|url=http://csvtu.ac.in/pdf_doc/affiliated%20_Poly_colleges%20with%20CSVTU_POLY_01.pdf|publisher=CSVTU|accessdate=9 July 2013|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130820202803/http://csvtu.ac.in/pdf_doc/affiliated%20_Poly_colleges%20with%20CSVTU_POLY_01.pdf|archivedate=20 August 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}[https://csvtuforum.co.in/ 9. CSVTU launch a Forum Community website for students] {{Swami Vivekananda}}\n{{Chhattisgarh Swami Vivekanand Technical University}}\n{{Universities in Chhattisgarh}}\n\n[[Category:Universities in Chhattisgarh]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 2005]]\n[[Category:Education in Bhilai]]\n[[Category:2005 establishments in India]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=August 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Infobox University\n|name           = Chhattisgarh Swami Vivekanand Technical University\n|image          = Chhattisgarh Swami Vivekanand Technical University transparent logo.png\n|motto          =\"Arise! Awake! and stop not until the goal is reached.\" \n|established    = {{start date|2005}}\n|vice_chancellor     = M.K. Verma \n|city           = [[Bhilai]], [[Chhattisgarh]], [[India]]\n|country        =India\n|students=\n|type           = [[Public university|Public]] [[State University]]\n|campus         = [[Urban areas|Urban]]\n|affiliations   = [[University Grants Commission (India)|UGC]], [[All India Council of Technical Education|AICTE]]\n|website= [http://www.csvtu.ac.in www.csvtu.ac.in]\n|logo           =|logo_size=250px\n|Address=}}\n'''Chhattisgarh Swami Vivekanand Technical University''' ('''CSVTU''') is a Public State University located in [[Bhilai]], [[Chhattisgarh]], [[India]]. On 30 April 2005, the foundation stone of the University was laid by the Prime Minister of India [[Manmohan Singh]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.csvtuforum.co.in/ew/|title=Chhattisgarh Swami Vi